nal identity and the identity of the countryside have been partly constructed through filmic representation, and how British rural films can allow us to further understand the relationship between the cultural identities of specific areas of Britain and the landscapes they inhabit.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLandscapes in motion pictures. 0aRural conditions in motion pictures. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aBritish.  aCinema.  aFilm.  aLandscape.  aPlace.  aRepresentation.  aRural.  aSpace.1 aBroughton, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHigson, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHockenhull, Stella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnston, Keith M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoody, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNewland, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNewland, Paul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPetrie, Duncan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRyall, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpeidel, Suzanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWoodward, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packagez978311128282440uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610468740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526104687423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526104687/original  a978-3-11-128282-4  Manchester University Press 2016 eBo